A total of 45 Fulani men are being interrogated about their mission to Okitipupa, headquarters of Okitipupa local government area of Ondo State. They were reportedly transported to the community at night and seen alighting from a truck by some youths. They were dumped near Army Barracks in Okitipupa town. Witnesses said the soldiers refused them further movement while security operatives including men of the Amotekun corps were called in. The source said the man that moved the men to the town, Fafoluyi Emmanuel, was immediately apprehended by Amotekun operatives. Chairman of Okitipupa local government, Mr Igbekele Akinrinwo, urged assured the men would be moved to Akure for further security checks and investigation.